iRight now, I'm gradually migrating my servers from Devuan Linux to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i[NixOS](https://nixos.org/). NixOS is a Linux distribution centered on		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ia set of Nix configuration files located in `/etc/nixos`, which is		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iused to install and configure the whole operating system. Because this		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iconfiguration set defines **ALL** config files and packages on the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isystem, as long as you use the same config files, you will absolutely		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iget the same operating system every time you reinstall. Nix		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iconfiguration language is also Turing complete, so you will be able to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
igenerate config files with Nix, no matter how complicated that		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isoftware is.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
