i> <https://discourse.nixos.org/t/how-to-make-uefis-grub2-menu-the-same-as-bioss-one/10074>		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iTherefore, NixOS doesn't need a rescue system in most cases, as it can		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
irecover itself with an older config state. Once the system is up, you		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ican proceed to redeploy the fixed config or continue to use the older		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isystem as if nothing has happened.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> Note that this NixOS mechanism is not a filesystem snapshot and		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> cannot rollback data files of programs.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
